1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:06,500
Did you know? This programming language
is written entirely in Sanskrit.

2
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:12,600
Its name is Sanskrita.
Watch — 'vada' means: speak.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,400
Variables, loops, functions —
all built on Panini's grammar.

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:23,000
0.1 plus 0.2 —
the answer: exactly 0.3.

5
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:27,700
Python gets this wrong!

6
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:34,600
And watch — it just recognized the meter of
the Bhagavad Gita's first verse: Anushtubh!

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:42,300
Sanskrita. Open source. Link below.
Jayatu Sanskritam!
